ies attest to the powerful social ferment of the past ten years in Taiwan, which have witnessed a revolution in discourses on sex and sexuality in the public sphere. Contributors: Chu T'ien-Wen, Qiu Miaojin, Chu T'ien-Hsin, Hsu Yoshen, Lin Yuyi, Lin Chun Ying, Chen Xue, Hong Ling, Chi Tawei, Wu Jiwen.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 0aChinese fictiony20th century. 0aChinese fictionzTaiwan. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aJiwen, Wu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLing, Hong, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartin, Fran, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartin, Fran.1 aMiaojin, Qiu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTawei, Chi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aT’Ien-Hsin, Chu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aT’Ien-Wen, Chu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aXue, Chen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYing, Lin Chun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYoshen, Hsu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYuyi, Lin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUHP eBook Package 2000-2013z978311056414308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Hawaii Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066325940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082486146940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824861469423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780824861469.jpg  a978-3-11